-- Biovail, HudBay, Thomson Creek, Toronto-Dominion: Canada Equity Preview
-- Elizabeth Stanton
-- 2010-06-21T12:46:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/biovail-hudbay-thomson-creek-toronto-dominion-canada-equity-preview.html

          
          
             Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  Canadian trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  
 Biovail Corp.  (BVF CT): Canada’s largest publicly traded
drugmaker, will merge with  Valeant Pharmaceuticals International 
(VRX US) of the U.S. Valeant shareholders will receive a one-
time cash dividend of $16.77 a share just before the deal
closes, plus Biovail stock valued at $26 a share at closing. The
transaction will add to per-share earnings for shareholders of
both companies within 12 months after the deal closes, Biovail
and Valeant said.  
 HudBay Minerals Inc.  (HBM CT): The copper and zinc producer
named  David Garofalo  as president and chief executive officer.
He also will be a director. Garofalo is a former senior vice
president and chief financial officer at  Agnico-Eagle Mines Ltd. 
(AEM CT)  
 Thomson Creek Metals Co.  (TCM CT): The molybdenum producer
with operations in Idaho, Pennsylvania and British Columbia was
upgraded to “buy” from “neutral” at UBS AG.  
 Toronto-Dominion Bank  (TD CT): Canada’s second-largest bank
filed a registration for $15 billion in debt securities.
Toronto-Dominion disclosed the plan in a U.S. regulatory filing.  
